# Personal config repository sync

- Personal Codex/Claude configuration source repository:
  `https://github.com/victor-lubn/codex-claude-config.git`
- Local clone path:
  `C:\a-phoenix\codex-claude-config`

When the user asks to add, update, save, or persist something "here", "in config",
"in Codex config", "in Claude config", or "in the personal config repo":

1. Update the local runtime config for both tools when the rule applies to both:
   Codex under `C:\Users\ViktarLubinski\.codex\rules` and Claude under
   `C:\Users\ViktarLubinski\.claude`.
2. Mirror the portable/safe version into `C:\a-phoenix\codex-claude-config`.
3. Keep Codex and Claude portable instructions aligned unless the user clearly
   asks for one tool only.
4. Do not copy secrets, auth files, sqlite state, sessions, logs, plugin cache,
   sandboxes, temp files, or attachments.
5. Commit the config repo change.
6. Push the config repo change to GitHub.

Before committing in the config repo, inspect local commit style with:

```powershell
git log --oneline -10
```

If the config repo has no stronger convention, use a clear simple commit message.
